We formalise our caluculus by equipping it with a set of rewrite
rules.  You should think of these in exactly the way that you think of
rewrite rules for the lambda calculus: you can apply any rewrite rule,
anywhere, at any time.  In particular, rewrite rules can be applied
to open terms, and under lambdas.  The rewrite rules are equivalences:
each rule is semantics-preserving if applied left-to-right or
right-to-left.  However, we intend that the left-to-right direction ``makes progress''.
